		<ul class='children'>
		<li class="comment even depth-2 parent" id="comment-16206">
				<div id="div-comment-16206" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
		<img alt='User' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c1fb5a7f85902e8a394b1e338823e6d5?s=32&amp;d=http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 avatar-default' height='32' width='32' />		<cite class="fn">User</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.engineyard.com/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/comment-page-1/#comment-16206">
			August 31, 2009 at 9:05 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Last I looked MongoDB didn&#039;t actually support partitioned queries except by pkey; hopefully this has changed.</p>

		<div class="reply">
		<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/?replytocom=16206#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-16206", "16206", "respond", "2126")'>Reply</a>		</div>
				</div>
		<ul class='children'>
		<li class="comment odd alt depth-3" id="comment-16208">
				<div id="div-comment-16208" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
		<a href='http://www.mongodb.org' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank' title='Visit dm_10gen&rsquo;s website' class='snap_noshots'><img alt='dm_10gen' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ccd9d3934901e0c96865f264851c8ddc?s=32&amp;d=http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 avatar-default' height='32' width='32' /></a>		<cite class="fn"><a href="http://www.mongodb.org" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outbound/commentauthor/www.mongodb.org');"  rel='external nofollow' class='url'>dm_10gen</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.engineyard.com/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/comment-page-1/#comment-16208">
			August 31, 2009 at 9:22 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>In mongodb you can do any query.  If one of the terms of the query is the partition key, the query will be executed on the smallest possible set of shards.  If the query is general it will go to all shards and collect the results. </p>
<p>MongoDB sharding is currently in alpha (the core database is full production now).</p>

		<div class="reply">
		<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/?replytocom=16208#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-16208", "16208", "respond", "2126")'>Reply</a>		</div>
				</div>
		</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-16211">
				<div id="div-comment-16211" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
		<img alt='joevandyk' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/57badfb3e8a4e8a81536f7dc6e47b812?s=32&amp;d=http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 avatar-default' height='32' width='32' />		<cite class="fn">joevandyk</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.engineyard.com/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/comment-page-1/#comment-16211">
			August 31, 2009 at 10:03 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>From mongo&#039;s website: &quot;Mongo does not support full master-master replication.  However, for certain restricted use cases master-master can be used.  Generally, we recommend one does not use the database in a master-master mode.&quot;</p>
<p>That&#039;s a bit different than what Cassandra offers, isn&#039;t it?</p>

		<div class="reply">
		<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/?replytocom=16211#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-16211", "16211", "respond", "2126")'>Reply</a>		</div>
