		<img alt='Michael Sheakoski' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/abb9cf617ce3ecffccb61a3acf12ccff?s=32&amp;d=http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 avatar-default' height='32' width='32' />		<cite class="fn">Michael Sheakoski</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.engineyard.com/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/comment-page-1/#comment-16233">
			September 1, 2009 at 2:38 am</a>		</div>

		<p>FYI if you search for Java Preferences in Spotlight, you can pick which version it will load first. In Snow Leopard I only see Java SE 6 so it shouldn&#039;t be an issue.</p>

		<div class="reply">
		<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/?replytocom=16233#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-16233", "16233", "respond", "2126")'>Reply</a>		</div>
