		<li class="comment even depth-2" id="comment-16356">
				<div id="div-comment-16356" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
		<img alt='Rhett' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/292ea489740972fd2437b28bbfbccac8?s=32&amp;d=http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 avatar-default' height='32' width='32' />		<cite class="fn">Rhett</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.engineyard.com/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/comment-page-1/#comment-16356">
			September 2, 2009 at 11:22 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Java Preferences is the Apple-supported way to go.  If you&#039;re using Java Preferences, you also want to set your JAVA_HOME like so: </p>
<p>export JAVA_HOME=`/usr/libexec/java_home` </p>
<p>(note the backticks).  Also, if you use Java Preferences to pick your JDK, you don&#039;t have to modify your PATH.  More info: </p>
<p><a href="http://lists.apple.com/archives/java-dev/2009/Jun/msg00139.html" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outbound/comment/lists.apple.com');" target="_blank"></a><a href="http://lists.apple.com/archives/java-dev/2009/Jun.." onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outbound/comment/lists.apple.com');" rel="nofollow">http://lists.apple.com/archives/java-dev/2009/Jun..</a>.</p>

		<div class="reply">
		<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/2009/cassandra-and-ruby-a-love-affair/?replytocom=16356#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-16356", "16356", "respond", "2126")'>Reply</a>		</div>
